<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-162-070 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 862 390</DOCID><JOURNAL>CVGIP: Graphical Models and Image Processing  May 1991 v53 n3p258(11).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Rule-based multitemplate edge detector. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brzakovic, D.; Patton, R.; Wang, R.L.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An edge detection algorithm is described that uses directionaltemplates of various sizes and rule-based decision making toassign confidence values to candidate edge pixels in the presenceof noise.andP;  The smallest template size provides localization ofedges; the largest provides immunity to noise; and theintermediate sizes provide stabilization.andP;  The rules refer tochanges in magnitudes of the cross-correlation coefficients anddetected edge orientations as the template size changes.andP;  Theconfidence value is assigned by the algorithm to each candidateedge pixel through application of rules to the results ofcross-correlating templates of various sizes with a pixelneighborhood.andP;  The confidence value reflects the likelihood of aparticular pixel being an edge pixel.andP;  An edge image is generatedby retaining edge pixels associated with high confidence values.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Rule-Based SystemsEdge DetectionImage ProcessingTheoretical ResearchNew TechniquePixelsImage GenerationMathematical ModelsAlgorithm Analysis.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Scheme used to cross-correlate templates of different sizes with apixel. (chart)Utilization of directional templates in edge detection. (chart)Detection of an edge in the presence of an additional edge.andO;(chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>